The paper focuses on binary code learning for nearest neighbor search problems, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method also involves graph-based approximation and optimization, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of ordinal constraints and ranking preservation is related to learning to rank (cs.IR) and similarity learning (cs.AI).
